The crisis rocking the major political parties in Oyo State has also extended to Oyo state chapter of Social Democratic Party (SDP) as the party also held parallel congresses to elect state executive members of the party. Sunday Independent gathered that the congresses became necessary in view of the forthcoming general elections in 2023. Two factions within the party on Saturday held parallel congresses where two executive members emerged. It was also learned that the two congresses that were held simultaneously at two different locations in Ibadan, the state capital. It was gathered that one of the congresses was held at National Museum of Unity, Aleshinloye, Ibadan while the second congress was held at Havanah Royale, besides University of Ibadan. The congress which took place at Aleshinloye produced Mr. Yinka Folahan as Chairman. The second congress which took place at Havanah Royale produced Mr. Kola Balogun as Chairman. Other members who will serve as members of Folahan’s faction are; Leye Egunobi who emerged as Secretary, Dasola Adebayo who emerged as Women leader, Otunba Tunde Laoye who emerged as Public Relations Officer, Princess Kemi Oshinowo who emerged as Organising Secretary and Akintan Oladele who emerged as Youths leader. POLL Folahan while speaking explained that the congress which produced him as Chairman was attended by all the party executive from the 33 local government areas in the state. He said that the congress was conducted by the outgoing Chairman of the party, Ambassador Olugbenga Curtis. According to him, “All the party executives from all the local government are there present and it was conducted by the outgoing Chairman”.